Slovakiaâ€™s inflation rate rose to a
28-month high of 3.7 percent in April from 3.6 percent in the
previous month, the statistics office said.  On a monthly basis, consumer prices in the euro-region
member advanced 0.4 percent in April, the Bratislava, Slovakia-
based office said today in a statement.  Advancing the most were prices of shoes and clothing, which
were up 2.1 percent on the month. Prices of alcohol and tobacco
advanced 1.4 percent, driven by an increase in excise taxes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
